reviews.review_text:
Best AUD's on the Archives Are consistently the Rango Keshavan audience recordings -- especially with Charlie Miller's mastering. This recording is so unbelievably spectacular, it is, por moi', the quintessence of pure recorded sound.

Rango nails it again. This is impeccable sound.

And if the sound is good for us listening today then it was probably good for them hearing it on stage. Perhaps when a band like this can hear themselves properly they usually play with verve and innovation. This 2 hr, 16 minute effort is no exception.

Dare to say that if you were sitting in the perfect listening vantage in this venue that this recording would be an acutely accurate representation of the sound there that day.

Thanks again to Rango, Charlie and the Archives.

Time for me to make a donation.
